  The maxim, education has no age barrier is more prominent among civil servants and public officials because there lies the path to any promotion in the service. The thirst for knowledge has forced a Permanent Secretary in a South-West state and his son to be classmates in a private university in Ogun State.  Few months ago, Politricks gathered that the Permanent Secretary (name withheld) and his son were both offered admission to study Law Degree in the institution and both of them wore matriculation gown at the matriculation ceremony of the institution. And since then, both father and son have being receiving lectures together under the same roof.  One wonders what will the nature of relationship between the father and son would be especially in the classroom, and among their coursemate.